Agile Frog.label: Agile frog
Agile Frog.description: The agile frog is a frog in the genus Rana in the family of the true frogs. Wikipedia

Caecilia tentaculata.label: Caecilia tentaculata
Caecilia tentaculata.description: Caecilia tentaculata is a species of amphibian in the Caeciliidae family. It is found in Brazil, Colombia, Ecuador, French Guiana, Peru, Suriname, Venezuela, possibly Bolivia, and possibly Guyana. Wikipedia

Calotriton.label: Calotriton
Calotriton.description: Calotriton is a genus of newts native to the Pyrenees and central Catalonia. These amphibians were formerly placed within genus Euproctus. Wikipedia

Dendrobates azureus.label: Blue poison dart frog
Dendrobates azureus.description: The blue poison dart frog or blue poison arrow frog is a poison dart frog found in the forests surrounded by the Sipaliwini savannah, which is located in southern Suriname and adjacent far northern Brazil. Wikipedia

Eastern newt.label: Eastern newt
Eastern newt.description: The eastern newt is a common newt of eastern North America. They frequent small lakes, ponds, and streams or near-by wet forests. Wikipedia

Euproctus.label: Euproctus
Euproctus.description:
Euproctus is a genus of salamander in the Salamandridae family. It contains the following species
Euproctus montanus – Corsican Brook Salamander
Euproctus platycephalus – Sardinian Brook Salamander Wikipedia

Gastric-brooding frog.label: Gastric-brooding frog
Gastric-brooding frog.description: The gastric-brooding frogs or platypus frogs were a genus of ground-dwelling frogs native to Queensland in eastern Australia. The genus consisted of only two species, both of which became extinct in the mid-1980s. Wikipedia

Golden poison frog.label: Golden poison frog
Golden poison frog.description: The golden poison frog, also known as the golden frog, golden poison arrow frog, or golden dart frog, is a poison dart frog endemic to the Pacific coast of Colombia. Wikipedia

Hellbender.label: Hellbender
Hellbender.description: The hellbender, also known as the hellbender salamander, is a species of giant salamander endemic to eastern North America. Wikipedia

Leptobrachium leucops.label: Leptobrachium leucops
Leptobrachium leucops.description: Leptobrachium leucops is a species of amphibian in the Megophryidae family. This toad was discovered by Bidoup Núi Bà National Park in Lâm Đồng Province, Central Highlands region of Vietnam by a group of ... Wikipedia

Microbrachis.label: Microbrachis
Microbrachis.description: Microbrachis is an extinct genus of lepospondyl amphibian from the Carboniferous period of what is now the Czech Republic. Wikipedia

Neurergus.label: Neurergus
Neurergus.description: Neurergus is a genus of salamanders, more specifically newts, in the Salamandridae family. They are found in the Middle East, and are bred in captivity for their bright colors. Wikipedia

Notophthalmus.label: Notophthalmus
Notophthalmus.description: Notophthalmus is a genus of newts known commonly as North American newts. There are three species. Wikipedia

Pool Frog.label: Pool Frog
Pool Frog.description: The Pool Frog is a European frog. It is one of only four amphibian species recognized by the UK government as protected under its Biodiversity Action Plan. Wikipedia

Rough-skinned newt.label: Rough-skinned newt
Rough-skinned newt.description: The rough-skinned newt is a North American newt known for the strong toxin exuded from its skin. Wikipedia

Siphonops annulatus.label: Siphonops annulatus
Siphonops annulatus.description: The ringed caecilian is a species of amphibian in the family Caeciliidae from South America. Wikipedia

Adenomera.label: Adenomera
Adenomera.description: Adenomera, sometimes known as tropical bullfrogs is a genus of leptodactylid frogs. These frogs are found in South America east of the Andes. The genus was until recently considered a synonym of Leptodactylus. Wikipedia

Adenomera hylaedactyla.label: Adenomera hylaedactyla
Adenomera hylaedactyla.description: Adenomera hylaedactyla is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family. It is found in Argentina, Bolivia, Brazil, Colombia, Ecuador, French Guiana, Guyana, Paraguay, Peru, Suriname, Trinidad and Tobago, and Venezuela. Wikipedia

Adenomera andreae.label: Adenomera andreae
Adenomera andreae.description: Adenomera andreae is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family. It is found in Bolivia, Brazil, Colombia, Ecuador, French Guiana, Guyana, Peru, Suriname, and Venezuela. Wikipedia

Adenomus kandianus.label: Adenomus kandianus
Adenomus kandianus.description: The Kandyan dwarf toad, Adenomus kandianus is a species of toad in the Bufonidae family endemic to Sri Lanka. It had been listed as extinct by the IUCN as there had been no record of the species since 1872. Wikipedia

Adenomus kelaartii.label: Adenomus kelaartii
Adenomus kelaartii.description: The Kelaart's toad Adenomus kelaartii is a species of toad in the Bufonidae family. It is endemic to Sri Lanka, where it exists in the south-west of the island at elevations between 30 and 1,230 m. Wikipedia

African bullfrog.label: African bullfrog
African bullfrog.description: The African bullfrog is a species of frog in the Ranidae family. It is also known as the pixie frog due to its Latin name. Wikipedia

Afrixalus.label: Afrixalus
Afrixalus.description:
Afrixalus is a genus of frog in the Hyperoliidae family. There are about 30 species.
Species include
Afrixalus aureus - golden banana frog
Afrixalus brachycnemis - lesser banana frog
Afrixalus clarkeorum ... Wikipedia

Afrixalus clarkeorum.label: Afrixalus clarkei
Afrixalus clarkeorum.description: Afrixalus clarkei is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family. Its common name is Clarke's banana frog. It is endemic to southwestern Ethiopia near Bonga and Bodare. Wikipedia

Afrixalus fornasini.label: Afrixalus fornasini
Afrixalus fornasini.description: Afrixalus fornasini is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family and is native to Africa. Its common name is Fornasini's spiny reed frog or the Greater Leaf-folding Frog Wikipedia

Afrixalus lindholmi.label: Afrixalus lindholmi
Afrixalus lindholmi.description: Afrixalus lindholmi is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family. It is endemic to Cameroon, where it occurs in marshes. Wikipedia

Afrixalus orophilus.label: Afrixalus orophilus
Afrixalus orophilus.description: Afrixalus orophilus is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family. It is found in Burundi, Democratic Republic of the Congo, Rwanda, and Uganda. Wikipedia

Afrixalus stuhlmanni.label: Afrixalus stuhlmanni
Afrixalus stuhlmanni.description: Afrixalus stuhlmanni is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family. It is found in Kenya, Tanzania, and Mozambique. Wikipedia

Afrixalus sylvaticus.label: Afrixalus stuhlmanni sylvaticus
Afrixalus sylvaticus.description:
Afrixalus stuhlmanni sylvaticus is a subspecies of frog in the Hyperoliidae family. Its common name is forest banana frog or forest spiny reed frog.
It is found in Kenya and Tanzania. Wikipedia

Afrixalus vibekensis.label: Afrixalus vibekensis
Afrixalus vibekensis.description: Afrixalus vibekensis is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family. It is confirmed to exist in two locations in Côte d'Ivoire and one in Ghana, and it possibly occurs in Guinea and Liberia. Wikipedia

Afrixalus weidholzi.label: Afrixalus weidholzi
Afrixalus weidholzi.description: Afrixalus weidholzi is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family. Its common name is Weidholz's banana frog. Wikipedia

Aglyptodactylus laticeps.label: Aglyptodactylus laticeps
Aglyptodactylus laticeps.description: Aglyptodactylus laticeps is a species of frog in the Mantellidae family. It is endemic to Madagascar. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical dry forests and intermittent freshwater marshes. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Aglyptodactylus securifer.label: Aglyptodactylus securifer
Aglyptodactylus securifer.description: Aglyptodactylus securifer is a species of frog in the Mantellidae family. It is endemic to Madagascar. Wikipedia

Albericus.label: Albericus
Albericus.description: Albericus is a genus of microhylid frogs endemic to New Guinea. These are small frogs with maximum body length around 27 mm. The genus was described in 1995, when three species in Cophixalus were separated as a new genus. Wikipedia

Alexteroon.label: Alexteroon
Alexteroon.description:
Alexteroon is a genus of frogs, commonly called midwife frogs, in the Hyperoliidae family. It contains these species
Alexteroon hypsiphonus
Alexteroon jynx
Alexteroon obstetricans Wikipedia

Alsodes barrioi.label: Alsodes barrioi
Alsodes barrioi.description: Alsodes barrioi is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family, endemic to Chile. Its natural habitat is temperate forests. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Alsodes gargola.label: Alsodes gargola
Alsodes gargola.description: Alsodes gargola is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family found in Argentina and possibly Chile. Its natural habitats are temperate forests, subtropical or tropical dry shrubland, rivers, freshwater lakes, and freshwater marshes. Wikipedia

Alsodes nodosus.label: Alsodes nodosus
Alsodes nodosus.description: Alsodes nodosus is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family found in Chile and possibly Argentina. Its natural habitats are temperate shrubland, rivers, and intermittent rivers. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Ansonia (genus).label: Ansonia
Ansonia (genus).description: Ansonia is a small genus of true toads found in South India, northern Thailand, Malay Peninsula, Tioman Island, Borneo,and Mindanao. These small forest species spawn in streams and have torrent-adapted tadpoles. Wikipedia

Amietia amieti.label: Amietia amieti
Amietia amieti.description: Amietia amieti is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family. It was formerly placed in the Ranidae family. Wikipedia

Ansonia hanitschi.label: Ansonia hanitschi
Ansonia hanitschi.description: Ansonia hanitschi is a species of toad in the Bufonidae family. It is found in Indonesia, Malaysia, and possibly Brunei. Wikipedia

Ansonia latidisca.label: Ansonia latidisca
Ansonia latidisca.description: Ansonia latidisca, commonly called the Sambas stream toad or Bornean rainbow toad, is a small true toad rediscovered in 2011 after being unseen since 1924. It is found in Indonesia and Malaysia. Wikipedia

Ansonia mcgregori.label: Ansonia mcgregori
Ansonia mcgregori.description: Ansonia mcgregori is a species of toad in the Bufonidae family. It is endemic to the Philippines. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical dry forests, subtropical or tropical moist lowland ... Wikipedia

Ansonia platysoma.label: Ansonia platysoma
Ansonia platysoma.description: Ansonia platysoma is a species of toad in the Bufonidae family. It is found in Malaysia and possibly Brunei. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests, subtropical or tropical moist montane forests, and rivers. Wikipedia

Ansonia spinulifer.label: Ansonia spinulifer
Ansonia spinulifer.description: Ansonia spinulifer is a species of toad in the Bufonidae family. It is found in Indonesia, Malaysia, and possibly Brunei. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests and rivers. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Ansonia tiomanica.label: Ansonia tiomanica
Ansonia tiomanica.description: Ansonia tiomanica is a species of toad in the Bufonidae family native to Malaysia. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests, rivers, inland karsts, and caves. Wikipedia

Aparasphenodon.label: Aparasphenodon
Aparasphenodon.description: Aparasphenodon is a genus of frogs in the Hylidae family, and are found southeastern Brazil, the Orinoco Basin, Venezuela and Colombia. These are tree-dwelling species usually hiding in the cisterns of epiphytic bromeliads. Wikipedia

Aparasphenodon venezolanus.label: Aparasphenodon venezolanus
Aparasphenodon venezolanus.description: Aparasphenodon venezolanus is a species of frog in the Hylidae family. It is found in Brazil, Colombia, and Venezuela. Wikipedia

Aplastodiscus perviridis.label: Aplastodiscus perviridis
Aplastodiscus perviridis.description: Aplastodiscus perviridis is a species of frog in the Hylidae family. It is found in Argentina, Brazil, and possibly Paraguay. Wikipedia

Aplastodiscus weygoldti.label: Aplastodiscus weygoldti
Aplastodiscus weygoldti.description: Aplastodiscus weygoldti is a species of frog in the Hylidae family. It is endemic to Brazil. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests and rivers. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Atelognathus patagonicus.label: Atelognathus patagonicus
Atelognathus patagonicus.description: Atelognathus patagonicus is a species of frog in the Batrachylidae family. It is endemic to Argentina. Wikipedia

Atelopus chiriquiensis.label: Atelopus chiriquiensis
Atelopus chiriquiensis.description: Atelopus chiriquiensis is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae. It is found in Costa Rica and Panama. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist montane forests and rivers. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Austrochaperina.label: Austrochaperina
Austrochaperina.description: Austrochaperina is a genus of microhylid frogs found on New Guinea, New Britain and Australia. Wikipedia

Austrochaperina pluvialis.label: Austrochaperina pluvialis
Austrochaperina pluvialis.description: Austrochaperina pluvialis, commonly known as the Rain Frog or White-browed Whistling Frog, is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family. It is endemic to Australia. Wikipedia

Banded bull frog.label: Banded bull frog
Banded bull frog.description: The banded bull frog is also known as the chubby frog, Asian painted frog, rice frog, or bubble frog. These frogs belonging to the narrow-mouthed frog family have round bodies with mahogany brown backs and cream stomachs. Wikipedia

Banded stream frog.label: Banded stream frog
Banded stream frog.description:
The banded stream frog is a species of frog in the Ranidae family. It is endemic to South Africa.
Its natural habitats are temperate forests, Mediterranean-type shrubby vegetation, rivers, and swamps. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Barbourula.label: Barbourula
Barbourula.description: Barbourula is a genus of amphibian commonly referred to as jungle toads. They are small toads of the fire-bellied toad family, Bombinatoridae, found in the Philippines and Borneo. Wikipedia

Barycholos.label: Barycholos
Barycholos.description: Barycholos is a genus of leptodactylid frogs found in Brazil and Ecuador. Wikipedia

Barycholos pulcher.label: Barycholos pulcher
Barycholos pulcher.description: Barycholos pulcher is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family. It is endemic to Ecuador. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests, plantations, heavily degraded former forest, and introduced vegetation. Wikipedia

Barycholos ternetzi.label: Barycholos ternetzi
Barycholos ternetzi.description: Barycholos ternetzi is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family. It is endemic to Peru. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical dry forests, moist savanna, subtropical or tropical moist ... Wikipedia

Barygenys.label: Barygenys
Barygenys.description: Barygenys is a genus of microhylid frogs. Wikipedia

Batrachophrynus brachydactylus.label: Batrachophrynus brachydactylus
Batrachophrynus brachydactylus.description: Batrachophrynus brachydactylus is an endangered species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family. This semi-aquatic frog is endemic to tributaries of Lake Junín in central Peru, where found at altitudes of 4,000–4,600 metres. Wikipedia

Batrachyla.label: Batrachyla
Batrachyla.description: Batrachyla is a genus of frogs in the Batrachylidae family. Sometimes known as the South American wood frogs, these frogs are distributed in southern South America. Wikipedia

Aplastodiscus ehrhardti.label: Aplastodiscus ehrhardti
Aplastodiscus ehrhardti.description: Aplastodiscus ehrhardti is a species of frog in the Hylidae family. It is endemic to Brazil. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests and intermittent freshwater marshes. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Aplastodiscus cavicola.label: Aplastodiscus cavicola
Aplastodiscus cavicola.description: Aplastodiscus cavicola is a species of frog in the Hylidae family. It is endemic to Brazil. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests and rivers. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Aphantophryne.label: Aphantophryne
Aphantophryne.description: Aphantophryne is a genus of microhylid frogs endemic to New Guinea. Originally described by Fry in 1917, Richard G. Zweifel considered in 1956 Aphantophryne synonymous to Cophixalus. Wikipedia
